g.aria-label: - No castling is allowed. - A pawn can promote to king. - There is no check or checkmate. - Capturing of the opponent's pieces is mandatory.

Losing chess (also known as antichess, the losing game, giveaway chess, suicide chess, killer chess, must-kill, take-all chess, take-me chess, capture chess or losums) is one of the most popular chess variants. The objective of each player is to lose all of their pieces or be stalemated.
Who loses all pieces including the king or cannot make a legal move, wins the game
